  "title": "bug: vue-instantsearch issues with vue 3.4",
  "body": "### 🐛 Current behavior\r\n\r\nWhen using the ais-configure component an error is thrown stating: \"The `searchParameters` option expects an object. [...]\".\r\n\r\nThe error is thrown in `instantsearch-js`:\r\nhttps://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/blob/1b8e1d9680ca141861c715c030448b114b96f435/packages/instantsearch.js/src/connectors/configure/connectConfigure.ts#L84-L88\r\n\r\nIt's seems that the object that are passed along from 'ais-configure'  is a Proxy instance, and then the `isPlainObject` fails.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### 🔍 Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/assets/1124666/74ec9269-b9e1-4cf7-920b-f3eaf68892ec)\r\n![algolia-500](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/assets/1124666/d94ae8dc-ed20-45c9-a549-3cb796296ca0)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Live reproduction\r\n\r\nhttps://codesandbox.io/p/devbox/jovial-ioana-g5j43k?file=%2Fsrc%2FApp.vue%3A23%2C36\r\n\r\n### 💭 Expected behavior\r\n\r\nShould render without error.\r\n\r\n### Package version\r\n\r\nvue-instantsearch 4.16.0\r\n\r\n### Operating system\r\n\r\nMacOS 13.2.1\r\n\r\n### Browser\r\n\r\nArc 1.37.0\r\n\r\n### Code of Conduct\r\n\r\n- [X] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct",
